-- Covidien quarterly net income climbs
-- 
-- Thu Feb 7, 2008 6:34am EST
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2008/02/07/us-covidien-results-idUSWNAS977820080207

 

 NEW YORK  (Reuters) - Covidien Ltd ( COV.N ) said on Thursday its fiscal first-quarter earnings rose, spurred by strong sales from its imaging solutions and medical devices business. 

 Net income in the quarter ended Dec 28, 2007 was $420 million, or 84 cents a share, compared with a year-ago profit of $338 million, or 68 cents a share. Excluding items, income from continuing operations was 59 cents a share, down from 69 cents a share, a year earlier. (Reporting by  Euan Rocha  and  Debra Sherman ; Editing by  Derek Caney )